        </div>
        <div class="risk-bar-track">
          <div class="risk-bar-fill" style="width:74%; background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--amber), #FFD080);"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="risk-desc">OPEC+ extended production cuts through Q2 2026. Tight supply against recovering global demand maintains upward pressure.</div>
        <div class="risk-expand" id="exp-opec">
          <div class="risk-detail">
            Saudi Arabia and Russia agreed in March 2026 to maintain cuts of 1.66 million barrels/day. This keeps global supply below demand, supporting Brent crude in the $88–96 range. Kenya's fuel import costs are directly indexed to Brent, meaning sustained OPEC+ cuts translate to structurally higher EPRA-set prices for the foreseeable future.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="risk-card" id="risk-ksh" onclick="toggleRisk('ksh')">
