          <div class="risk-bar-fill" style="width:68%; background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--amber), #FFD080);"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="risk-desc">Kenya buys crude in USD. A weaker shilling means higher landed costs even if crude prices stay flat. KES is at 135/USD.</div>
        <div class="risk-expand" id="exp-ksh">
          <div class="risk-detail">
            The Kenyan shilling has depreciated ~8% against the dollar in 2025–26. Since all crude purchases are dollar-denominated, shilling weakness acts as a multiplier on global price shocks. FuelPulse tracks the live KES/USD rate and incorporates it into every prediction — something no other tool does for Kenya.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

